# Team Task Tracker API

## Overview

A REST API for managing tasks within an organization. The system supports authentication, role-based access control (RBAC), task management, status transitions, validation, and API documentation.

---

## Tech Stack

* Node.js
* Express.js
* MongoDB
* Mongoose
* JWT Authentication
* Zod Validation
* Swagger/OpenAPI
* Docker

---

## Features

### Authentication

* User Registration
* User Login
* JWT Access Token
* Refresh Token Rotation

### Authorization

Roles Supported:

* ADMIN
* MANAGER
* MEMBER

Role Permissions:

| Role    | Permissions                           |
| ------- | ------------------------------------- |
| ADMIN   | Full access to organization resources |
| MANAGER | Manage projects and tasks             |
| MEMBER  | View and update assigned tasks        |

RBAC is enforced using middleware.

---

## Task Management

### CRUD Operations

* Create Task
* Get Task
* Update Task
* Delete Task

### Task Fields

* title
* description
* priority
* status
* assignee
* dueDate

### Status Transition Rules

Allowed transitions:

TODO → IN_PROGRESS → IN_REVIEW → DONE

Any active state → BLOCKED

Only the assignee or a MANAGER can advance task status.

---

## Pagination & Filtering

Supported query parameters:

* page
* limit
* status
* priority
* assignee

Example:

GET /api/tasks?page=1&limit=10

GET /api/tasks?status=TODO

GET /api/tasks?priority=HIGH

---

## Validation

Request validation is implemented using Zod.

Example validation response:

{
"status": 400,
"code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
"message": "Title is required"
}

---

## Error Handling

Consistent error responses are implemented across all endpoints.

Example:

{
"status": 400,
"code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
"message": "dueDate must be a future date"
}

---

## Database Design

### Collections

#### User

* name
* email
* password
* role
* organizationId
* refreshToken

#### Organization

* name

#### Task

* title
* description
* priority
* status
* assignee
* dueDate
* createdBy
* organizationId

### Indexes

Indexes added on:

* status
* assignee
* dueDate

### Design Decision

Tasks reference Users and Organizations using ObjectId relationships rather than embedding data.

This approach:

* avoids duplication
* improves maintainability
* supports efficient querying across collections

---

## API Documentation

Swagger UI available at:

/api-docs

---

## Running Locally

Install dependencies:

npm install

Start server:

npm run dev

---

## Docker

Build and run:

docker compose up --build

---

## Future Improvements

Given the assignment timeline, I prioritized implementing the core functionality and focused on correctness, security, and maintainability.

With additional time, I would add:

* Redis caching with cache invalidation
* Integration tests
* Analytics endpoint
* WebSocket notifications
* Advanced audit logging
* Rate limiting
* CI/CD pipeline

